title: Kennedy.2015.06.10.WS.SDTV.x264-XAiO
description:
"Kennedy" is a news panel show hosted by Kennedy Montgomery. Kennedy Montgomery is a libertarian that you may recognize from 90's MTV, Stossel, and the Independents.

_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2

Kennedy does her monologue on Lindsey Graham's presidential bid & the potential of having rotating first ladies. (Graham's idea. Haha.)

Tonights panel consists of CHARLES COOKE, JIMMY FAILLA, and MONICA CROWLEY. First on the docket is the New York Times recent finacial discoveries about Marco Rubio. San Francisco wants mandatory warnings on sugary snack ads and New York wants menus with items that have more of a teaspoon of salt to contain a warning. The panel predictably thinks it is dumb.

GUY BENSON and MARY KATHARINE HAM are here to discuss their new book "End of Discussion" & the recent controvesy involving some not so PC comments by Sienfeld. 

JOHN STOSSEL stops by to discuss his next special "Green Tyranny".

The panel returns to talk about Grooms taking the Bride's name. Pot camp opens up in Colorado. They can't sell weed, but it's highly encouraged to bring your own. (Nice.) The issue of legalization is quickly brought up. Monica hates it. Kennedy loves it. Up next - airlines want to shrink the standard bag size allowed.

BILL NYE is in the studio. Not to fight - but to show off a neat new deployed spacecraft. Very good segment, they mostly talk about solar sails. Check out planetary.org!

On tonight's nightcap Kennedy goes after the recent idiotic anti-states rights statement made by Chris Christie against marijuana legalization. He says that if he's president, it wont be allowed.
